  ;; ===================================================================
  ;; TEXT ANNOTATIONS (design notes on the schematic sheet)
  ;; ===================================================================

  (text "W7HAK Go-Box: Pi Zero W Telemetry HAT\n\nThis HAT sits on the Pi Zero W 40-pin GPIO header and provides:\n  - JST-XH 5-pin connector (J1) for BMS battery cell taps + ground\n  - JST-XH 6-pin connector (J2) for ADS1115 ADC module\n  - 4-channel resistor ladder voltage dividers (1% precision)\n  - Hardware RC low-pass filters (~16 Hz cutoff) on every ADC channel\n  - 4.7kΩ pull-up for DS18B20 1-Wire bus\n  - 0.1µF decoupling cap on ADS1115 VDD\n\nPin Mapping:\n  J1 (BMS Taps):  1=Cell4(14.4V) 2=Cell3(10.8V) 3=Cell2(7.2V) 4=Cell1(3.6V) 5=GND\n  J2 (ADS1115):   1=A0 2=A1 3=A2 4=A3 5=VDD(3.3V) 6=GND\n  GPIO Header:    Pin1=3.3V  Pin3=SDA  Pin5=SCL  Pin9=GND  Pin7=GPIO4(1-Wire)"
    (at 20 -140 0)
    (effects (font (size 2 2)) (justify left))
  )

  (text "DESIGN NOTES:\n- All divider & filter resistors are 1% precision metal film\n- All capacitors rated minimum 25V (LiFePO4 pack reaches 14.6V)\n- RC filter cutoff: f = 1/(2π×1kΩ×10µF) ≈ 16 Hz\n- Board dimensions: 65mm × 30mm (Pi Zero HAT form factor)\n- Mount with 2x20 pin female header (pin 1 aligned with Pi pin 1)\n- 4 mounting holes: M2.5, matching Pi Zero mounting pattern"
    (at 20 -185 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.8 1.8)) (justify left))
  )

)
